    "reason": "Correct a pre-implementation semantic defect: the probability that an action is the best of long, abstain, and short is not the probability that the same side has positive after-cost return when both sides can be positive. Add a separately calibrated, shared side-profit head for expected-return estimation while retaining three-action probabilities exclusively for routing. Data, costs, chronology, risk controls, and authority-denial contracts remain unchanged."
